<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-27T12:00:00-05:00">July 27,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:35 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>82. I have just conferred with Under Secretary for Foreign Affairs. In
                            his opinion, since the transfer of authority has followed the
                            Constitution, the question of recognition is not raised.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>